---
import { getGlobalNews } from '../lib/global-news';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const globalNews = await getGlobalNews();
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section
    class="section-root section-root-accent"
    style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;min-height:70vh;min-height:70svh;display:flex;align-items:center;"
  >
    <div
      aria-hidden="true"
      style="position:absolute;inset:0;background-image:linear-gradient(to right, var(--grid-line-color) 1px, transparent 1px),linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--grid-line-color) 1px, transparent 1px);background-size:clamp(24px,4vw,44px) clamp(24px,4vw,44px);pointer-events:none;"
    ></div>
    <div class="container-root" style="position:relative;z-index:1;padding-block:var(--space-4);">
      <p class="kicker">Nigeria chapter · PauseAI Global</p>
      <h1 class="heading-accent" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Frontier AI must not be deployed without democratic control.</h1>
      <p style="max-width:62ch;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:var(--space-3);">
        The most powerful AI systems are being developed faster than safety can be guaranteed or oversight can be secured.
        PauseAI Nigeria mobilizes citizens, researchers, and policymakers to ensure Nigeria shapes—not inherits—the rules
        that govern superhuman AI. We call for a coordinated global pause until robust safety guarantees and democratic
        accountability are in place.
      </p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-2);flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/take-action#join" class="btn-root btn-primary">Join the chapter</a>
        <a href="/why-pause" class="btn-root btn-secondary">Why pause AI?</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root" style="padding-block:var(--space-3);">
    <div class="container-root stats-grid">
      <article class="card-root card-pad"><h3>110k+</h3><p>Global signatories</p></article>
      <article class="card-root card-pad"><h3>30+</h3><p>National chapters</p></article>
      <article class="card-root card-pad"><h3>1st</h3><p>West Africa chapter</p></article>
      <article class="card-root card-pad"><h3>0</h3><p>Days to waste</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root section-root-accent">
    <div class="container-root cards-grid">
      <article class="card-root card-pad">
        <h3>Upcoming Event</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">No event scheduled yet. Follow communities for first notice.</p>
        <a href="/events">View events</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card-root card-pad">
        <h3>Policy Watch</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">Track NITDA, NCC, National Assembly and state-level AI activity.</p>
        <a href="/nigeria-ai-policy">Open policy tracker</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card-root card-pad">
        <h3>Take Action</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">Join the chapter, contact lawmakers, and plug into local groups.</p>
        <a href="/take-action">Act now</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Nigeria must shape global AI governance, not inherit it</h2>
      <p>
        Nigeria's digital economy is on track to exceed half a trillion dollars in value this decade. That scale
        makes Nigeria a major stakeholder in how frontier AI is governed. Yet without coordinated international action,
        Nigeria risks seeing unsafe AI systems deployed by external actors, with outcomes written by nations and corporations
        far from Nigerian communities.
      </p>
      <p>
        A temporary pause on frontier AI development is a practical step to establish safety guarantees and democratic oversight
        before deployment. It gives Nigeria—alongside other nations—time to:
      </p>
      <ul style="margin: var(--space-1) 0; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
        <li>Build policy capacity and independent audit frameworks</li>
        <li>Protect financial systems, elections, and civic institutions from AI-enabled harms</li>
        <li>Participate in international treaty negotiations from a position of principle</li>
        <li>Ensure AI innovation serves Nigerian development priorities, not external interests</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/why-pause">Read the full case</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root section-root-accent">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>From PauseAI Global</h2>
      <div class="news-grid">
        {
          globalNews.map((item) => (
            <article class="card-root card-pad">
              <h3>{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="news-meta">{item.pubDate}</p>
              <a href={item.link} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read update</a>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-root">
    <div class="container-root">
      <h2>Join the PauseAI Global newsletter</h2>
      <p>Get global updates and campaign news directly from PauseAI.</p>
      <a class="btn-root btn-primary" href="https://pauseai.substack.com/?email=" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Join newsletter</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .kicker {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    color: var(--brand-green);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
  }
  .stats-grid,
  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .news-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .card-pad {
    padding: var(--space-2);
  }
  .news-meta {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0.7rem;
  }
</style>
